North Carolina Early Voting Statistics

Last Report: 09/15/2020
Source: https://dl.ncsbe.gov/?prefix=ENRS/2020_11_03/

North Carolina is the first state to begin general election voting. Election officials sent ballots to voters on September 4.

Rejected

Nearly all 989 rejected mail ballots in the midst of the pandemic are for the reason noted as “WITNESS INFO INCOMPLETE”. North Carolina election officials are required by state law to follow up with these voters. If you are a North Carolina voter concerned about your mail ballot, you can track the status of your ballot at the North Carolina State Board of Elections website.
